Public Service Credit Union (PSCU) is a member-owned financial cooperative for current and former public servants and their families where our members save and borrow with us along with accessing other financial services.
We are committed to protecting the privacy and security of your personal information and take our responsibilities under applicable data protection law, including the EU General Data Protection Regulation (“GDPR”) and implementing legislation such as the Data Protection Act 2018 very seriously.
Our suite of Privacy Notices provides details of how we process your personal data in order to open your account, provide services to you and other general purposes. If you apply for a loan, the Lending Agreement Privacy Notice will provide more information to take account of further processing that may be necessary.
Download PS2414 General Privacy Notice (Long Form)
Download PS2414 Membership Privacy Notice
Download PS2414 Lending Agreement Privacy Notice
Download PS2414 Junior Privacy Notice
Should you have any queries or a complaint regarding your rights under GDPR or require more details about how Public Service Credit Union processes your personal data, you can contact the Credit Union’s Data Protection Officer at the address below.
